      "title": "1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 1",
      "pageid": 16655,
      "revid": 97246,
      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Problem\">Problem</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Problem\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Prove that the number <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/f/b/4fb9deda28dd806ab7c5291115fb23684e753144.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\underbrace{111\\ldots 11}_{1997}\\underbrace{22\\ldots 22}_{1998}5$\" style=\"vertical-align: -22px\" width=\"151\" height=\"34\" /> (which has 1997 of 1-s and 1998 of 2-s) is a perfect square.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution\">Solution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Solution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The number <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/f/b/4fb9deda28dd806ab7c5291115fb23684e753144.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\underbrace{111\\ldots 11}_{1997}\\underbrace{22\\ldots 22}_{1998}5$\" style=\"vertical-align: -22px\" width=\"151\" height=\"34\" /> can be rewritten as\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/4/6/54696215394625b9fe9c92fea1795883671747c4.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[(10^{3995} + 10^{3994} + \\cdots 10^{1999}) + 2(10^{1998} + 10^{1997} + \\cdots 10) + 5.\\]\" width=\"476\" height=\"19\" />\nThis number has a few geometric series and can be written as\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/6/c/46c4d6c0bde9a09cf9aade636850bc920c8c894f.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\frac{10^{1999}(10^{1997} - 1)}{9} + 2 \\cdot \\frac{10(10^{1998} - 1)}{9} + 5.\\]\" width=\"330\" height=\"39\" />\nSimplifying results in\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/c/a/dcadf5d34ef6c1ef48ed7cec82691ecf6ea3ad00.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\frac{10^{3996} - 10^{1999} + 2 \\cdot 10^{1999} - 20 + 45}{9}\\]\" width=\"284\" height=\"39\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/f/6/5f63da4fe953d33291b863fbca1d2b53d2a3f4da.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\frac{10^{3996} + 10^{1999} + 25}{9}.\\]\" width=\"159\" height=\"39\" />\nNotice that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/0/4/50438197eb466ea8d3cc3cdd518452a4c4c57f2d.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$10^{3996} = (10^{1998})^2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"135\" height=\"19\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/d/0/8d0a4e515d604254af98a4c3bc40969689883e39.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$10^{1999} = 10 \\cdot 10^{1998}.$\" style=\"vertical-align: 0px\" width=\"150\" height=\"15\" />  That means we can \"factor\" the numerator, and doing so results in\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/4/b/94b794a546fb81e9480fe21cce5215a9e4179d8d.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\frac{(10^{1998} + 5)^2}{9}\\]\" width=\"98\" height=\"39\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/1/6/516d1e36bc9b273ceb2967a267e0359076964446.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\left(\\frac{10^{1998} + 5}{3}\\right)^2.\\]\" width=\"117\" height=\"46\" />\nSince <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/e/7/0e72cb7382363dad6123031d004b78026c8e69a6.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$10^{1998} + 5$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"76\" height=\"16\" /> is divisible by 3, we conclude that the number <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/f/b/4fb9deda28dd806ab7c5291115fb23684e753144.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\underbrace{111\\ldots 11}_{1997}\\underbrace{22\\ldots 22}_{1998}5$\" style=\"vertical-align: -22px\" width=\"151\" height=\"34\" /> is a perfect square.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_Also\">See Also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See Also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:95%; border:1px solid black; width:80%;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background:#ccf;text-align:center;\" colspan=\"3\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO\" title=\"1998 JBMO\">1998 JBMO</a></b> (<b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems\">Problems</a></b> • <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://artofproblemsolving.com/community/c13_contests\">Resources</a>)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"50%\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\">Preceded&#160;by<br /><b>First Problem</b>\n</td>\n<td width=\"50%\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\">Followed&#160;by<br /><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_2\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 2\">Problem 2</a></b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">1</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_2\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 2\">2</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_3\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 3\">3</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_4\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 4\">4</a> <b></b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/JBMO_Problems_and_Solutions,_with_authors\" title=\"JBMO Problems and Solutions, with authors\"> All JBMO Problems and Solutions</a></b>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240907154135\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.022 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.024 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 144/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 435/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 839/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 43/2097152 bytes\nHighest 