  "1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 3": {
    "parse": {
      "title": "1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 3",
      "pageid": 19574,
      "revid": 133785,
      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Find all pairs of positive integers <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/5/3/e53b1fe25be1c679117fb44a6a886fe1247d189a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(x,y)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"40\" height=\"18\" /> such that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/8/a/98ac839a2ad0030079cd9730649546627b3937a9.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[x^y = y^{x - y}.\\]\" width=\"81\" height=\"16\" />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution\">Solution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_3&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Solution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Note that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/f/9/8f9af910fe749481919573c0dd2b132118f19d19.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$x^y$\" width=\"17\" height=\"12\" /> is at least one. Then <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/8/e/68ebc5a323bd8bdc6b6b47c81c68a5be8ab4dfec.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$y^{x - y}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"34\" height=\"16\" /> is at least one, so <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/7/a/37ae1ec4f112be920af3d1d6e78e5a4c546d6c47.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$x \\geq y$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"43\" height=\"15\" />.\n</p><p>Write <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/7/2/472d8b6e49e70c3ac6dcef9ec76330ddff47b22d.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$x = a^{b+c}, y = a^c$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"124\" height=\"19\" />, where <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/7/9/979d4f1460e025b7d85916ac72c7924d9c9e6736.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gcd(b, c) = 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"97\" height=\"18\" />. (We know that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/1/3/8136a7ef6a03334a7246df9097e5bcc31ba33fd2.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"10\" height=\"14\" /> is nonnegative because <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/1/b/c1b87945430c01d2919b5c2393a4c68db8801b88.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$x\\geq y$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"43\" height=\"15\" />.) Then our equation becomes <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/c/0/ec04289200e05e50d04a4b5d44a056b4a967de09.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a^{(b+c)*a^c} = a^{c*(a^{b+c} - a^c)}$\" width=\"170\" height=\"18\" />. Taking logarithms base <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/7/d/c7d457e388298246adb06c587bccd419ea67f7e8.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"11\" height=\"10\" /> and dividing through by <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/1/a/d1ad4eb8a558e07fcace68a9648832e6ed240abd.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a^c$\" width=\"15\" height=\"12\" />, we obtain <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/8/8/3884c7a206aea7a1034b3c9ff4ed935928ef7f6e.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b + c = c*(a^b - 1)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"147\" height=\"20\" />.\n</p><p>Since <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/3/7/3372c1cb6d68cf97c2d231acc0b47b95a9ed04cc.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$c$\" width=\"8\" height=\"8\" /> divides the RHS of this equation, it must divide the LHS. Since <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/7/9/979d4f1460e025b7d85916ac72c7924d9c9e6736.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\gcd(b, c) = 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"97\" height=\"18\" /> by assumption, we must have <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/3/5/5351998230e216d9d0f2884c159326cfe6622263.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$c = 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: 0px\" width=\"40\" height=\"12\" />, so that the equation reduces to <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/4/3/9437212ad4c8b7c740ef3cf62c4c2a56a24361b9.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b + 1 = a^b - 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"110\" height=\"17\" />, or <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/3/7/037096765258b2500eb3ff27cad035305e435adc.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b + 2 = a^b$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"78\" height=\"17\" />. This equation has only the solutions <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/b/a/1ba5933c1b5354ef8b26eea5fbb5a0ce2c506559.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b = 1, a = 3$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"91\" height=\"16\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/8/d/a8ded7c60cc13668f6fae30d1387d3ddb480b94c.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b = 2, a = 2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"94\" height=\"18\" />.\n</p><p>Therefore, our only solutions are <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/7/0/770e5250c225c01414222c6794227a9e0a48c7dc.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$x = 3^{1 + 1} = 9, y = 3^1 = 3$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"192\" height=\"18\" />, and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/b/4/3/b43eb1411432722f3f30f9f7c4bedab3b289a01c.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$x = 2^{2+1} = 8, y = 2^1 = 2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"192\" height=\"18\" />, and we are done.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_3&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:95%; border:1px solid black; width:80%;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background:#ccf;text-align:center;\" colspan=\"3\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO\" title=\"1998 JBMO\">1998 JBMO</a></b> (<b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems\">Problems</a></b> • <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://artofproblemsolving.com/community/c13_contests\">Resources</a>)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"50%\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\">Preceded&#160;by<br /><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_2\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 2\">Problem 2</a></b>\n</td>\n<td width=\"50%\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\">Followed&#160;by<br /><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_4\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 4\">Problem 4</a></b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_1\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 1\">1</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_2\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 2\">2</a> <b>•</b> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">3</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_4\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 4\">4</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_5&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 5 (page does not exist)\">5</a><b></b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/JBMO_Problems_and_Solutions,_with_authors\" title=\"JBMO Problems and Solutions, with authors\"> All JBMO Problems and Solutions</a></b>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240907211013\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.030 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.033 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 233/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 619/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 912/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 40/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 3882/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    1.912      1 Template:JBMO_box\n100.00%    1.912      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki-wiki_:pcache:idhash:19574-0!canonical and timestamp 20240907211013 and revision id 133785\n -->\n"
