  "1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 4": {
    "parse": {
      "title": "1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 4",
      "pageid": 19845,
      "revid": 134744,
      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Do there exist 16 three digit numbers, using only three different digits in all, so that the all numbers give different residues when divided by 16?\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution\">Solution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_4&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Solution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Let the three different digits be <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/c/c/acc6d9a6172d35127b6cb37ea92192caf7029a54.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a, b, c$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"43\" height=\"18\" />. \n</p><p>If <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/c/c/acc6d9a6172d35127b6cb37ea92192caf7029a54.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a, b, c$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"43\" height=\"18\" /> all have the same parity, then all sixteen numbers will also have the same parity. But then they can only cover at most 8 residues modulo 16, so they cannot have distinct residues by the <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/Pigeonhole_principle\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pigeonhole principle\">pigeonhole principle</a>.\n</p><p>Suppose that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/c/c/acc6d9a6172d35127b6cb37ea92192caf7029a54.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a, b, c$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"43\" height=\"18\" /> do not all have the same parity. If two are even and one is odd, then twelve of the eighteen possible three-digit numbers formed with <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/c/c/acc6d9a6172d35127b6cb37ea92192caf7029a54.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a, b, c$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"43\" height=\"18\" /> will be even and six will be odd. But this means that there are not enough odd numbers to fill the 8 odd residues modulo 16, so it will not be possible to select 16 three digit numbers with this property in this case. \n</p><p>Similarly, if two are odd and one is even, then twelve of the eighteen possible three-digit numbers formed with <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/c/c/acc6d9a6172d35127b6cb37ea92192caf7029a54.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a, b, c$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"43\" height=\"18\" /> will be odd and six will be even. But this means that there are not enough even numbers to fill the 8 even residues modulo 16, so it will not be possible to select 16 three digit numbers with this property in this case.\n</p><p>Therefore, we conclude that it is impossible to select 16 such numbers.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_4&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:95%; border:1px solid black; width:80%;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background:#ccf;text-align:center;\" colspan=\"3\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO\" title=\"1998 JBMO\">1998 JBMO</a></b> (<b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems\">Problems</a></b> • <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://artofproblemsolving.com/community/c13_contests\">Resources</a>)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"50%\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\">Preceded&#160;by<br /><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_3\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 3\">Problem 3</a></b>\n</td>\n<td width=\"50%\" align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\">Followed&#160;by<br /><b>Last Problem</b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_1\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 1\">1</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_2\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 2\">2</a> <b>•</b> <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/1998_JBMO_Problems/Problem_3\" title=\"1998 JBMO Problems/Problem 3\">3</a> <b>•</b> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">4</a> <b></b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><b><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/JBMO_Problems_and_Solutions,_with_authors\" title=\"JBMO Problems and Solutions, with authors\"> All JBMO Problems and Solutions</a></b>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240907103014\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.015 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.016 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 78/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 291/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 838/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 42/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 885/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    1.869      1 Template:JBMO_box\n100.00%    1.869      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki-wiki_:pcache:idhash:19845-0!canonical and timestamp 20240907103014 and revision id 134744\n -->\n"
